[[!meta title="Hiding the boot menu"]]

A common [customisation request](http://webconverger.com/buy/) is to disable
the [[boot_menu|boot]] prompt, in order to:

* Make boots quicker
* Disallow any [[boot]] time alterations

This is done by replacing the syslinux theme with `progress-appliance` in
[auto/config](https://github.com/Webconverger/Debian-Live-config/blob/master/webconverger/auto/config)
when [[building_Webconverger|develop]].

	--syslinux-theme progress-appliance

[[Thanks|acknowledgements]] to [Daniel on
Debian-Live](http://lists.debian.org/debian-live/2012/01/msg00027.html).

## Without rebuilding

You can also try modify the ISO images as described in [[develop]] and change `isolinux/isolinux.cfg ` to values in your `live.cfg`.

	default linux
	label linux
		kernel /live/vmlinuz1
		append initrd=/live/initrd1.img boot=live quiet ...the rest of your options
